29typedef enum {
30 dns_ssumatchtype_name = 0,
31 dns_ssumatchtype_subdomain = 1,
32 dns_ssumatchtype_wildcard = 2,
33 dns_ssumatchtype_self = 3,
34 dns_ssumatchtype_selfsub = 4,
35 dns_ssumatchtype_selfwild = 5,
36 dns_ssumatchtype_selfkrb5 = 6,
37 dns_ssumatchtype_selfms = 7,
38 dns_ssumatchtype_subdomainms = 8,
39 dns_ssumatchtype_subdomainkrb5 = 9,
40 dns_ssumatchtype_tcpself = 10,
41 dns_ssumatchtype_6to4self = 11,
42 dns_ssumatchtype_external = 12,
43 dns_ssumatchtype_local = 13,
44 dns_ssumatchtype_selfsubms = 14,
45 dns_ssumatchtype_selfsubkrb5 = 15,
46 dns_ssumatchtype_max = 15, /* max value */
47
48 dns_ssumatchtype_dlz = 16 /* intentionally higher than _max */
49} dns_ssumatchtype_t;
50
51isc_result_t
52dns_ssutable_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_ssutable_t **table);
53/*%<
54 * Creates a table that will be used to store simple-secure-update rules.
55 * Note: all locking must be provided by the client.
56 *
57 * Requires:
58 *\li 'mctx' is a valid memory context
59 *\li 'table' is not NULL, and '*table' is NULL
60 *
61 * Returns:
62 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS
63 *\li ISC_R_NOMEMORY
64 */
65
66isc_result_t
67dns_ssutable_createdlz(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_ssutable_t **tablep,
68 dns_dlzdb_t *dlzdatabase);
69/*%<
70 * Create an SSU table that contains a dlzdatabase pointer, and a
71 * single rule with matchtype dns_ssumatchtype_dlz. This type of SSU
72 * table is used by writeable DLZ drivers to offload authorization for
73 * updates to the driver.
74 */
75
76void
77dns_ssutable_attach(dns_ssutable_t *source, dns_ssutable_t **targetp);
78/*%<
79 * Attach '*targetp' to 'source'.
80 *
81 * Requires:
82 *\li 'source' is a valid SSU table
83 *\li 'targetp' points to a NULL dns_ssutable_t *.
84 *
85 * Ensures:
86 *\li *targetp is attached to source.
87 */
88
89void
90dns_ssutable_detach(dns_ssutable_t **tablep);
91/*%<
92 * Detach '*tablep' from its simple-secure-update rule table.
93 *
94 * Requires:
95 *\li 'tablep' points to a valid dns_ssutable_t
96 *
97 * Ensures:
98 *\li *tablep is NULL
99 *\li If '*tablep' is the last reference to the SSU table, all
100 * resources used by the table will be freed.
101 */
102
103isc_result_t
104dns_ssutable_addrule(dns_ssutable_t *table, bool grant,
105 const dns_name_t *identity, dns_ssumatchtype_t matchtype,
106 const dns_name_t *name, unsigned int ntypes,
107 dns_rdatatype_t *types);
108/*%<
109 * Adds a new rule to a simple-secure-update rule table. The rule
110 * either grants or denies update privileges of an identity (or set of
111 * identities) to modify a name (or set of names) or certain types present
112 * at that name.
113 *
114 * Notes:
115 *\li If 'matchtype' is of SELF type, this rule only matches if the
116 * name to be updated matches the signing identity.
117 *
118 *\li If 'ntypes' is 0, this rule applies to all types except
119 * NS, SOA, RRSIG, and NSEC.
120 *
121 *\li If 'types' includes ANY, this rule applies to all types
122 * except NSEC.
123 *
124 * Requires:
125 *\li 'table' is a valid SSU table
126 *\li 'identity' is a valid absolute name
127 *\li 'matchtype' must be one of the defined constants.
128 *\li 'name' is a valid absolute name
129 *\li If 'ntypes' > 0, 'types' must not be NULL
130 *
131 * Returns:
132 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS
133 *\li ISC_R_NOMEMORY
134 */
135
136bool
137dns_ssutable_checkrules(dns_ssutable_t *table, const dns_name_t *signer,
138 const dns_name_t *name, const isc_netaddr_t *addr,
139 bool tcp, const dns_aclenv_t *env,
140 dns_rdatatype_t type, const dst_key_t *key);
141/*%<
142 * Checks that the attempted update of (name, type) is allowed according
143 * to the rules specified in the simple-secure-update rule table. If
144 * no rules are matched, access is denied.
145 *
146 * Notes:
147 * In dns_ssutable_checkrules(), 'addr' should only be
148 * set if the request received via TCP. This provides a
149 * weak assurance that the request was not spoofed.
150 * 'addr' is to to validate dns_ssumatchtype_tcpself
151 * and dns_ssumatchtype_6to4self rules.
152 *
153 * In dns_ssutable_checkrules2(), 'addr' can also be passed for
154 * UDP requests and TCP is specified via the 'tcp' parameter.
155 * In addition to dns_ssumatchtype_tcpself and
156 * tcp_ssumatchtype_6to4self rules, the address
157 * also be used to check dns_ssumatchtype_local rules.
158 * If 'addr' is set then 'env' must also be set so that
159 * requests from non-localhost addresses can be rejected.
160 *
161 * For dns_ssumatchtype_tcpself the addresses are mapped to
162 * the standard reverse names under IN-ADDR.ARPA and IP6.ARPA.
163 * RFC 1035, Section 3.5, "IN-ADDR.ARPA domain" and RFC 3596,
164 * Section 2.5, "IP6.ARPA Domain".
165 *
166 * For dns_ssumatchtype_6to4self, IPv4 address are converted
167 * to a 6to4 prefix (48 bits) per the rules in RFC 3056. Only
168 * the top 48 bits of the IPv6 address are mapped to the reverse
169 * name. This is independent of whether the most significant 16
170 * bits match 2002::/16, assigned for 6to4 prefixes, or not.
171 *
172 * Requires:
173 *\li 'table' is a valid SSU table
174 *\li 'signer' is NULL or a valid absolute name
175 *\li 'addr' is NULL or a valid network address.
176 *\li 'aclenv' is NULL or a valid ACL environment.
177 *\li 'name' is a valid absolute name
178 *\li if 'addr' is not NULL, 'env' is not NULL.
179 */
180

184/*% Accessor functions to extract rule components */
185dns_name_t * dns_ssurule_identity(const dns_ssurule_t *rule);
186/*% Accessor functions to extract rule components */
187unsigned int dns_ssurule_matchtype(const dns_ssurule_t *rule);

189dns_name_t * dns_ssurule_name(const dns_ssurule_t *rule);
190/*% Accessor functions to extract rule components */
191unsigned int dns_ssurule_types(const dns_ssurule_t *rule,
192 dns_rdatatype_t **types);

194isc_result_t dns_ssutable_firstrule(const dns_ssutable_t *table,
195 dns_ssurule_t **rule);
196/*%<
197 * Initiates a rule iterator. There is no need to maintain any state.
198 *
199 * Returns:
200 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
201 *\li #ISC_R_NOMORE
202 */
203
204isc_result_t dns_ssutable_nextrule(dns_ssurule_t *rule,
205 dns_ssurule_t **nextrule);
206/*%<
207 * Returns the next rule in the table.
208 *
209 * Returns:
210 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
211 *\li #ISC_R_NOMORE
212 */
213
214bool
215dns_ssu_external_match(const dns_name_t *identity, const dns_name_t *signer,
216 const dns_name_t *name, const isc_netaddr_t *tcpaddr,
217 dns_rdatatype_t type, const dst_key_t *key,
218 isc_mem_t *mctx);
